---
description: Enforces consistent React component creation patterns using named exports with explicit props typing and destructured parameters to ensure maintainable and predictable component interfaces across the codebase
globs: **/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---

Export Pattern:
- Always use `export function` syntax
- Never use default exports
- Use named exports consistently

Props Pattern:
- Use props object as first parameter
- Add type directly in destructuring
- Define separate props type interface
- Destructure props in parameter list

Example:
```tsx
type MyComponentProps = {
  prop1: string;
  prop2: number;
  prop3: number;
};

export function MyComponent({ prop1, prop2, prop3 }: MyComponentProps) {
  return <div>{prop1}</div>;
}
```